</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="102" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
When 
<bibRefCitation author="Melo, JIM" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="285 - 289" publicationUrl="10.1007/s12225-009-9109-3" refId="B44" refString="Melo, JIM, Semir, J, 2009. Two new species and new combinations in Euploca (Heliotropiaceae). Kew Bulletin 64 (2): 285 - 289, DOI: 10.1007/s12225-009-9109-3" title="Two new species and new combinations in Euploca (Heliotropiaceae)." url="10.1007/s12225-009-9109-3" volume="64" year="2009">Melo and Semir (2009</bibRefCitation>
: 289) transferred 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium ternatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ternatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium ternatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Vahl, MH" journalOrPublisher="Moeller, Copenhagen" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 106" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/118639page/313/mode/1up" refId="B68" refString="Vahl, MH, 1794. Symbolae botanicae. Moeller, Copenhagen: 1 - 106, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/118639page/313/mode/1up" title="Symbolae botanicae" url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/118639page/313/mode/1up" year="1794">Vahl (1794</bibRefCitation>
, 3: 21) to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they did not cite synonyms and they overlooked the case of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Tournefortia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tournefortia humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Tournefortia humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. There had been a doubt about the exact identity of the Linnean species (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Arnold Arboretum" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="111 - 188" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/part/18048/summary" refId="B29" refString="Johnston, IM, 1949. Studies in the Boraginaceae XVIII. Boraginaceae of the southern West Indies. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 30: 111 - 188, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/part/18048/summary" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae XVIII. Boraginaceae of the southern West Indies." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/part/18048/summary" volume="30" year="1949">Johnston 1949</bibRefCitation>
: 136; 
<bibRefCitation author="Foerther, H" journalOrPublisher="Sendtnera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="35 - 241" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" refId="B15" refString="Foerther, H, 1998. Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae). Sendtnera 5: 35 - 241, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" title="Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" volume="5" year="1998">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förther">Foerther</normalizedToken>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
: 190), but the typification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Tournefortia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tournefortia humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Tournefortia humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. by Miller (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cafferty, S" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="799 - 805" publicationUrl="10.2307/4135454" refId="B3" refString="Cafferty, S, Jarvis, CE, 2004. Typification of Linnaean plant names in Boraginaceae. Taxon 53 (3): 799 - 805, DOI: 10.2307/4135454" title="Typification of Linnaean plant names in Boraginaceae." url="10.2307/4135454" volume="53" year="2004">Cafferty and Jarvis 2004</bibRefCitation>
: 804) placed clearly that species in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium ternatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ternatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium ternatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Vahl (non 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium humile" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lam.). The epithet of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Tournefortia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tournefortia humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Tournefortia humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could not be transferred to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but there is no previous 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the priority rule dictates the adoption of the new combination (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J" journalOrPublisher="Koeltz, Koenigstein" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" publicationUrl="http://www.iapt-taxon.org/nomen/main.php" refId="B42" refString="McNeill, J, Barrie, FR, Buck, WR, Demoulin, V, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Marhold, K, Prado, J, Prud'Homme van Reine, WF, Smith, GF, Wiersema, JH, Turland, NJ, 2012. Regnum Vegetabile 154. In: International Code of Nomenclature for Algae, Fungi, and Plants (Melbourne Code). Koeltz, Koenigstein, http://www.iapt-taxon.org/nomen/main.php" title="Regnum Vegetabile 154" url="http://www.iapt-taxon.org/nomen/main.php" volumeTitle="International Code of Nomenclature for Algae, Fungi, and Plants (Melbourne Code)." year="2012">McNeill et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 11.4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
Because the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Tournefortia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tournefortia humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Tournefortia humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. or/and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium humile" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) R.Br. ex Roem. &amp; Schult. (1819, 4: 37; non Lam., 1791: 393) have been used in synonymy (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="3 - 73" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" refId="B26" refString="Johnston, IM, 1928. Studies in the Boraginaceae VII. The South American Species of Heliotropium. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium 81: 3 - 73, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VII. The South American Species of Heliotropium." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" volume="81" year="1928">Johnston 1928</bibRefCitation>
: 69; 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Arnold Arboretum" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="111 - 188" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/part/18048/summary" refId="B29" refString="Johnston, IM, 1949. Studies in the Boraginaceae XVIII. Boraginaceae of the southern West Indies. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 30: 111 - 188, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/part/18048/summary" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae XVIII. Boraginaceae of the southern West Indies." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/part/18048/summary" volume="30" year="1949">1949</bibRefCitation>
: 135; and especially the recent revision of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Foerther, H" journalOrPublisher="Sendtnera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="35 - 241" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" refId="B15" refString="Foerther, H, 1998. Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae). Sendtnera 5: 35 - 241, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" title="Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" volume="5" year="1998">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förther">Foerther</normalizedToken>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
: 190, 234; and the typification Miller, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cafferty, S" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="799 - 805" publicationUrl="10.2307/4135454" refId="B3" refString="Cafferty, S, Jarvis, CE, 2004. Typification of Linnaean plant names in Boraginaceae. Taxon 53 (3): 799 - 805, DOI: 10.2307/4135454" title="Typification of Linnaean plant names in Boraginaceae." url="10.2307/4135454" volume="53" year="2004">Cafferty and Jarvis 2004</bibRefCitation>
: 804); because it is a Linnean name; and because the authors of the new combination 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca ternata" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ternata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca ternata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Melo, JIM" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="285 - 289" publicationUrl="10.1007/s12225-009-9109-3" refId="B44" refString="Melo, JIM, Semir, J, 2009. Two new species and new combinations in Euploca (Heliotropiaceae). Kew Bulletin 64 (2): 285 - 289, DOI: 10.1007/s12225-009-9109-3" title="Two new species and new combinations in Euploca (Heliotropiaceae)." url="10.1007/s12225-009-9109-3" volume="64" year="2009">Melo and Semir 2009</bibRefCitation>
: 289) should have been aware of that name, there are little chances to make a successful proposal to conserve 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca ternata" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ternata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca ternata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
